   <text>
      <body>
         <pb n="1r" facs="lf_pDas_1669_dai_lns235ms_w_r.jpg"/>
         
         <div xml:id="orig_div1" xml:lang="ara" type="invocation" rend="top centre">
            <p>هو</p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div1" corresp="#orig_div1">
            <p>He [God] is</p>
         </div>

         <div xml:id="orig_div2" xml:lang="per" type="maintext">
            <p>
               <lb/>متصدیان مهمات حال و استقبال پرگنه
               <placeName ref="#pgDhar">دهار</placeName>
                سرکار
                <placeName ref="#mandu">مندو</placeName>
                بدانند که موازی پنج بیگه
               <lb/> زمین بنجر خارج جمع بجهت احداث باغ حسب الضمن از موضع
               <placeName ref="#maliwada">مالیواده</placeName>
                عمله پرگنه مذکور
               <lb/> به
               <persName ref="#nathmal">نتهمل</persName>
                پسر چودهری
               <persName ref="#purshottamDas">پرسوتم داس</persName>
                بتصدق فرق مبارک بندگان حضرت سلیمن منزلت
               <lb/>مقرر نموده شد که بخاطر جمع احداث باغ نماید که هچکس از محصول وغیره آراضی
               <lb/>مسطور مشار الیه مزاحم نشوند و حاصلات آنرا بتصرف او واگذارند که بدعاگوی
               <lb/>دوام دولت ابد پیوند اشتغال نماید تحریر فی التاریخ 
               <gap/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div2" corresp="#orig_div2">
            <p>
               <lb/>Important officials of the present and future of <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>, <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_sarkar">sarkar</ref> <placeName ref="#mandu">Mandu</placeName>, know that <measure type="land" quantity="5" unit="bigha">five</measure> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_bigha">bighas</ref> of fallow land, 
               <lb/>[which is] exempt from taxes, is allocated for the construction of a garden, according to the [details] on the reverse, from the village <placeName ref="#maliwada">Maliwada</placeName> in the administration of the said <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref>
               <lb/>to <persName ref="#nathmal">Nathmal</persName>, son of <persName ref="#purshottamDas">Purshottam Das</persName> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_chaudhri">chaudhri</ref>, as charity by the servants of the blessed head [the ruler], who is like Lord Suleiman<note>This is likely a reference to the biblical king Solomon, celebrated for his wisdom.</note>;
               <lb/>so that with settled mind he constructs the garden such that nobody
               <lb/>will disturb the said land of the said person [<persName ref="#nathmal">Nathmal</persName>] because of taxes etc. And the yield from that land should be given over to him so that
               <lb/>he can engage himself in praying that the longevity of the sovereignty be infinite. Written on the date <gap/><note>No date of composition appears after this phrase. The date of 1669 CE has been ascribed based on the approximate period of <persName ref="#nathmal">Nathmal's</persName> activities.</note>
            </p>
         </div>
         
         <div xml:id="orig_div3" xml:lang="per" type="authorisation" rend="top right margin">
            <p>
               <lb/>چون از پیشگاه خلافت در باب
               <lb/>احداث باغات بجهت رفاهت مترددان
               <lb/>حکم است بتصدق فرق مبارک اشرف
               <lb/>مقرر شد
               <g type="#baiz">بیض</g>
               <lb/><stamp type="seal"><mentioned>
                  <persName ref="#muhibbAli">محب علی</persName>
                  مرید
                  <persName ref="#aurangzebAlamgir">عالمگیر</persName>
                  شاه
               </mentioned></stamp></p></div>
            
         <div xml:id="trans_orig3" corresp="#orig_div3">
            <p> 
               <lb/>Since from the court of governance, the
               <lb/>the construction of a garden for the relief of travelers
               <lb/>is ordered, it is allocated in charity.
               <lb/><g type="#baiz">Ended.</g>
               <lb/><stamp type="seal">Round black ink seal<mentioned><persName ref="#muhibbAli">Muhibb Ali</persName>
               disciple of <persName ref="#aurangzebAlamgir">Alamgir</persName> Shah</mentioned></stamp>
            </p>
         </div>

         <pb n="1v" facs="lf_pDas_1669_dai_lns235ms_w_v.jpg"/>

         <div xml:id="orig_div4" xml:lang="per" type="laterAddition" rend="top right">
            <p>پروانه بنام
               <persName ref="#nathmal">نتهمل</persName>
                باغ
                <placeName ref="#maliwada">مالیواده</placeName>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div4" corresp="#orig_div4">
            <p><ref type="glossary" target="#gl_parvana">Parvana</ref> in the name of
               <persName ref="#nathmal">Nathmal</persName>
                [for] a garden [in]
               <placeName ref="#maliwada">Maliwada</placeName>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="orig_div5" xml:lang="per" type="clericalNotes" rend="middle right">
            <p>
               <lb rend="empty"/>مقرر ضمن از موضع مالیواده عمله
               <lb rend="empty"/>پرگنه دهار بجهته باغ به نتهمل مقرر نموده شد
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div5" corresp="#orig_div5">
            <p><lb rend="empty"/>Confirmed by the <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_zimn">zimn</ref>, [to wit] from the village <placeName ref="#maliwada">Maliwada</placeName> in the administration of 
               <lb rend="empty"/><ref type="glossary" target="#gl_pargana">pargana</ref> <placeName ref="#pgDhar">Dhar</placeName>, [land] for a garden is assigned to <persName ref="#nathmal">Nathmal</persName>. 
            </p>
         </div>

         <div xml:id="orig_div6" xml:lang="per" type="clericalNotes" rend="bottom centre">
            <p><app><rdg cert="low">ارازی</rdg>
               <rdg cert="high">موازی</rdg></app>
               <measure type="land" unit="bigha" quantity="5">پنج بیگه</measure>
               <gap/>
            </p>
         </div>
         <div xml:id="trans_div6" corresp="#orig_div6">
            <p><measure type="land" unit="bigha" quantity="5">5</measure> <ref type="glossary" target="#gl_bigha">bighas</ref> [of] land <gap/> </p>
         </div>
      </body>
